title: God of War Ragnarok: The Mythology Behind Thor
description:
God of War Ragnarök will soon give us the showdown to end all showdowns: the Norse Gods will finally face their final battle, with Kratos and Atreus in the mix for good measure. 

The god of thunder himself, Thor, is one of the major players in Norse mythology, and will butt heads with Kratos in Sony Santa Monica’s latest. So, let’s become the Gods of Lore as we take a look at how Thor initially appeared in Norse Mythology, discuss how that compares to what we already know about the thunder god in the game, and what that might mean for his ultimate fate as the end times, Ragnarok itself, thunders closer.

title: SAS Soldier Breaks Down CoD Modern Warfare SAS Missions | Expert Reacts
description:
Mark "Billy" Billingham served in the British SAS for over 17 years. He was responsible for planning and executing strategic operations across the world, and has led countless hostage rescues.

Since leaving the military he has worked as both a celebrity bodyguard, appears on Channel 4's "SAS: Who Dares Wins", "SAS Australia", and has just released his latest book "Survive To Fight".

Today he's joining us once again to break down and react to some of the most iconic missions from the Call of Duty franchise, including CoD 4, Modern Warfare 2, and Modern Warfare 2019

title: Silent Hill 2 Remake - What Can We Expect From Bloober Team? | MindGames
description:
Ever since the release of Layers of Fear, Bloober's games have been obsessed with getting you inside the damaged minds of their characters–sometimes literally. However, their games have also attracted criticism for their sometimes troubling messaging around trauma and mental health.

We spoke to Mateusz Lenart, Lead Director of the upcoming Silent Hill 2 Remake, about the origins of Layers of Fear, Bloober's horror philosophy, and how they hope to make psychological horror games that get inside the player's head too.

title: Firearms Expert Reacts To Call of Duty: Warzone’s Guns PART 2
description:
